tps:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/oguzeroglu\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/oguzeroglu\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars3.githubusercontent.com\/u\/15003836?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/oguzeroglu","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/oguzeroglu\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/oguzeroglu","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/oguzeroglu\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE1MDAzODM2","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/oguzeroglu\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/oguzeroglu\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/oguzeroglu\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"oguzeroglu","type":"User","id":15003836,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/oguzeroglu\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/oguzeroglu\/orgs"}},{"index":4,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"> AFAIK there's no difference between the TGA format and the PNG format if the GPU is concerned as all textures are ultimately converted to a format like DXT or BC5 when being sent to GPU (I might be wrong here).\r\n\r\nTexture compression does not happen automatically. So referring to S3TC in this issue does not make sense.","created_at":"2018-08-16T12:38:39.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/14716#issuecomment-413531188","id":413531188,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14716","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQxMzUzMTE4OA==","updated_at":"2018-08-16T13:22:41.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/413531188","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/12612165?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/Mugen87","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEyNjEyMTY1","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"Mugen87","type":"User","id":12612165,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/orgs"}},{"index":5,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"@Mugen87 Yes, you're right that's why I wrote I might be wrong here :) . I'm not sure about the format but I read somewhere that even though the image is a compressed image like JPEG, it does not matter for the GPU, it takes the same space as any other format when being uploaded to GPU if the texture is not properly compressed (like DXT).\r\n\r\nI probably should convert the TGAs to PNGs anyway because the repository should take as little space as possible.","created_at":"2018-08-16T12:49:59.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/14716#issuecomment-413534178","id":413534178,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14716","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQxMzUzNDE3OA==","updated_at":"2018-08-16T12:55:35.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/413534178","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/oguzeroglu\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/oguzeroglu\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars3.githubusercontent.com\/u\/15003836?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/oguzeroglu","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/oguzeroglu\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/oguzeroglu","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/oguzeroglu\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE1MDAzODM2","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/oguzeroglu\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/oguzeroglu\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/oguzeroglu\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"oguzeroglu","type":"User","id":15003836,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/oguzeroglu\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/oguzeroglu\/orgs"}},{"index":6,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"JPEG is no real texture compression format. Since the size of a compressed pixel in JPEG varies, the GPU has to decompress the entire image for random access (which is necessary due to the massive parallel processing of shaders). Block-based texture compression formats like S3TC, ETC1, PVRTC and ASTC ensure that all texels allocate the same amount of data space within a texture. So there is no decompression necessary when uploading the texture. In this way, they allocate much less memory on the GPU since decompression happens on-the-fly when accessing the texture data.","created_at":"2018-08-16T13:16:01.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/14716#issuecomment-413541635","id":413541635,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14716","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQxMzU0MTYzNQ==","updated_at":"2018-08-16T13:24:11.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/413541635","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/12612165?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/use