","body":"Setting ambient light to `0xffffff` is not appropriate. It also defeats the purpose to use it as the only light source with `MeshPhongMaterial`.\r\n\r\nYou need to add a direct light source to your scene. If you do that, you will see there is something wrong with your normals.\r\n\r\nMy conjecture is your normal map is only appropriate for a non-displaced mesh.","created_at":"2018-08-19T14:39:30.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/14716#issuecomment-414132141","id":414132141,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14716","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQxNDEzMjE0MQ==","updated_at":"2018-08-19T14:39:30.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/414132141","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":19,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"@WestLangley What do you mean by \"something is wrong with your normals\"? I think the problem here is that in this demo OrbitControls are used so the object itself is not moving but the camera is moving. When you put a directional light to a specific position without updating its position you'd see only one side of the cube is being illuminated. Maybe that's what you meant? I don't want to put 6 directional lights to the scene.\r\n\r\nThe reason I'm using the MeshPhongMaterial here is to have that sweet emissive intensity effect. I'm using high quality textures here and the object looks good to me (Scifi vibes). I don't want to focus too much on non geometry related issues in THIS PR which is titled \"CPU Displacement Calculation\", I did this to demonstrate how displacement can be done on geometry level using Javascript (without GLSL).\r\n\r\nThanks for the feedback about the emissive parameter, I wasn't aware of that. I did not see the 2 other remarks of that issue though. I don't know why you wrote \"this is the 3rd time I have mentioned this\"","created_at":"2018-08-19T15:08:19.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/14716#issuecomment-414133999","id":414133999,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14716","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQxNDEzMzk5OQ==","updated_at":"2018-08-19T15:08:55.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/414133999","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/oguzeroglu\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/oguzeroglu\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars3.githubusercontent.com\/u\/15003836?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/oguzeroglu","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/oguzeroglu\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/oguzeroglu","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/oguzeroglu\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE1MDAzODM2","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/oguzeroglu\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/oguzeroglu\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/oguzeroglu\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"oguzeroglu","type":"User","id":15003836,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/oguzeroglu\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/oguzeroglu\/orgs"}},{"index":20,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"Your only light source is ambient light. It does not respond to normals, so your model renders flat -- like it would with `MeshBasicMaterial`.\r\n\r\nOnce a direct light source is added, and the ambient light is reduced, it seems to me your normals are not correct in parts of the model. For example, parallel to a face.\r\n\r\nIf you only want a single direct light source, you can use this pattern:\r\n```javascript\r\nscene.add( camera );\r\n\r\ncamera.add( new THREE.PointLight( 0xffffff, 1 ) );\r\n```\r\n>I don't know why you wrote \"this is the 3rd time I have mentioned this\"\r\n\r\nIt appears a reviewer's inline feedback can be lost if you replace\/refactor large chunks of code.","created_at":"2018-08-19T21:18:50.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/14716#issuecomment-414156682","id":414156682,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14716","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQxNDE1NjY4Mg==","updated_at":"2018-08-19T21:18:50.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/414156682","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_ur